parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the front brake to fail to engage, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front brake lever is unable to be squeezed
the front brake fails to engage
the motorcycle is unable to come to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the engine to die or lose power while in motion, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine dies or loses power while in motion
the throttle position closes and does not accept inputs from the accelerator
the motorcycle goes into "limp home" mode
the motorcycle loses power while accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the motorcycle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls while in motion
the motorcycle loses power while accelerating
the motorcycle feels like it's running on one cylinder

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM plug can cause the vehicle to buck and run erratically, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.

The failure of the throttle control actuator can cause the vehicle to enter limp mode, resulting in a loss of throttle response, which can lead to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
The sudden and unexpected blowout of the rear tire can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The rear tire suddenly blows out without warning
causing the vehicle to lose control
resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to the rider.
